# Generated eval artifacts. These are committed on purpose, but they are written
# by Python (`json.dumps(..., indent=2)`, which emits no trailing newline), so
# reformatting them only holds until the next run regenerates them:
#   baseline.json          <- `make eval-baseline` (cp of eval/summary.json)
#   benchmark_results.json <- backend/eval/benchmark_strategies.py
#   case_study/*           <- backend/eval/case_study/reproduce.sh
# Leaving them byte-identical to what the harness emits also keeps eval diffs
# readable, which is the whole point of pinning them.
backend/eval/baseline.json
backend/eval/benchmark_results.json
backend/eval/case_study/clean.summary.json
backend/eval/case_study/regressed.summary.json
backend/eval/case_study/comment.md

# Grafana dashboard export — round-trips through the Grafana UI, so it should
